						<summary>

						<p>On the north base of the Maṇḍūkanāthēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Rājarāja I. Year 27: 1011-12 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This inscription begins with the <hi rend="italic">praśasti Tirumagaḷ pōla</hi> of the king.</p>						

						<p>This records the gift of 90 sheep for a perpetual lamp to god Māndai Nakkar of Māvaṇḍūr, a hamlet of Madhurāntaka-chaturvēdimaṅgalam.</p>						

						</summary>
